Table 1. Comparison with the most prominent annotated aerial data sets. 'Altitude' and 'Angle' indicate whether or not there are precise 
altitude and angle view information available. 'Other meta' refers to time stamps, GPS, and IMU data and in the case of object tracking can 
also mean attribute information about the sequences. The values with stars have been estimated based on ground truth bounding box sizes 
and corresponding real world object sizes (for altitude) and qualitative estimation of sample images (for angle). For DOTA and Airbus 
Ship the range of altitudes is not available because these are satellite-based data sets.
